HEADWORD: Guttatrap
<hw>Gut"ta*trap</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The inspissated
juice of a tree of the genus <gen>Artocarpus</gen> (<spn>A.
incisa</spn>, or breadfruit tree), sometimes used in making birdlime, on
account of its glutinous quality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gutter</ent>⟦br⟧
